# Plot the data
for ticker in df['tic'].unique():
    subset = df[df['tic'] == ticker]
    plt.plot(subset['date'], subset['close'], label=ticker)

# Set the locator
locator = mdates.YearLocator()  # Locate ticks at the start of every year
plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(locator)

# Set the formatter
formatter = mdates.DateFormatter('%Y')  # Format ticks to display just the year
plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_formatter(formatter)

plt.title('Closing Prices Over Time for Each Stock')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Closing Price')

# Rotate and align the tick labels so they look better
plt.gcf().autofmt_xdate()

plt.tight_layout()

plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plotting each stock's closing prices over time
num_tickers = len(df['tic'].unique())
fig, axes = plt.subplots(num_tickers, 1, figsize=(14, 7*num_tickers))
for i, ticker in enumerate(df['tic'].unique()):
    subset = df[df['tic'] == ticker]
    axes[i].plot(subset['date'], subset['close'], label=ticker)
    axes[i].set_title(f'Closing Prices Over Time for {ticker}')
    axes[i].set_xlabel('Date')
    axes[i].set_ylabel('Closing Price')
    axes[i].xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.YearLocator())
    axes[i].xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y'))
    axes[i].legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

def download_baseline(ticker, start_date, end_date):
    df = yf.download(ticker, start=start_date, end=end_date)
    df.reset_index(inplace=True)
    df.rename(columns={
        'Date': 'date',
        'Close': 'close',
        'Open': 'open',
        'High': 'high',
        'Low': 'low',
        'Adj Close': 'adj close',
        'Volume': 'volume'
    }, inplace=True)
    df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date'])
    return df

# Function to scale the 'close' prices for comparison
def scale_baseline(baseline_df, strategy_df):
    initial_amount = strategy_df['account_value'].iloc[0]
    scaling_factor = initial_amount / baseline_df['close'].iloc[0]
    baseline_df['close_scaled'] = baseline_df['close'] * scaling_factor
